detaileddescription.para:
Angular Distribution: The polar angle $ 	heta $ (relative to the local magnetic field) is sampled based on the angular dependence of the synchrotron emissivity $ j_
u(	heta) $. A second rejection sampling loop ensures that: \[ 	ext{rand} <  rac{j_
u(	heta)}{j_{
u, max}} \] where $ j_{
u, max} $ is the emissivity at $ 	heta = \pi/2 $.
